# {{project-name | title_case}}

A jackdaw game generated from the
[jackdaw-template-game](https://github.com/jbuehler23/jackdaw_template_game)
template.

## Status

Jackdaw's Play-in-Editor (PIE) runtime — the part that actually
*runs* your game inside the editor on a worker thread with a
shared scene — is under construction. Until it lands, game
projects scaffold as regular extensions so you can still write
Bevy code against the editor.

Writing your systems inside `GamePlugin` means the migration when
PIE ships will be a one-line change: swap the `JackdawExtension`
impl at the bottom of `src/lib.rs` for a
`jackdaw_game::export_game!` invocation, and your plugin will
start getting driven by jackdaw's SubApp runner.

## Build and install

Same as extensions for now:

1. Open jackdaw.
2. **File → Extensions → Build from project folder…**
3. Select this project's root directory.

The project builds and live-loads. Once PIE ships, the Play button
in the editor toolbar will drive your game instead.
